column1: 13,http://www.armslist.com/posts/4206013,For Sale:  Ruger 22/45 Mk III & 950 rounds .22LR,"North, Columbus, Ohio",$ 400,"Listed On: Friday, April 3, 2015",Handguns,Ruger                                                                                ,22 Long Rifle                                                                                ,no type,Pistol,"As you can see from the pictures, this is modified a bit. I attached an aftermarket compensator, top rail mount, Hogue grips, internal magazine safety disconnect removed (aftermarket hammer bushing), and does come with the Burris Fastfire III (specs online). I've done a lot to such an inexpensive little .22 ""plinker"", but it makes for a great shooting experience too. I've shot well over 1,000 rounds with this and it shows a little bit. It has some scuff marks on the backstrap. I also have the original plain metal sights and the factory hammer bushing in the original box. Also includes the factory zip-up travel pouch, and I have a .22 Bore Snake with it too.

This all includes 600 rounds of CCI MINI-MAG .22LR ammo, 250 rounds of Federal Premium .22LR ammo, 50 rounds of Winchester Power-Point .22LR ammo, and 50 rounds of CCI Stinger .22LR ammo. That's 950 rounds of ammo included! This is a my last to own .22lr gun.
$400 for it all."

The CZ 85 Combat adds a fully adjustable rear sight, extended magazine release, drop-free magazine and overtravel adjustment on the trigger. The Combat designation comes from the lack of a firing pin block safety, allowing the replacement of the firing pin without tools.

The rear sight is adjustable for elevation and windage, and the trigger for overtravel regulation. An extended magazine catch, elimination of the magazine brake and ambidextrous controlling elements directly predispose this model for sport shooting competitions.

Ambidextrous features include safety levers, slide stop levers and a reversible magazine release. The lack of a firing pin safety gives the 85 Combat a slight advantage in the trigger pull department, making it a long-time favorite of competition shooters.
